1. Add Lombok Dependency

If you’re using Maven, add this to your pom.xml:

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
    <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>
    <version>1.18.34</version> <!-- latest stable -->
    <scope>provided</scope>
</dependency>

2. Enable Annotation Processing in Your IDE

IntelliJ IDEA
Go to Settings → Build, Execution, Deployment → Compiler → Annotation Processors
Check "Enable annotation processing".

3. Use Lombok Annotations

Some commonly used annotations are:
@Getter / @Setter → Generates getter and setter methods.
@ToString → Generates toString().
@EqualsAndHashCode → Generates equals() and hashCode().
@NoArgsConstructor / @AllArgsConstructor / @RequiredArgsConstructor → Generates constructors.
@Data → Combination of @Getter, @Setter, @EqualsAndHashCode, @ToString, and @RequiredArgsConstructor.
@Builder → Creates builder pattern.
@Slf4j → Creates a logger instance.
